Overview
This project provides a practical design and implementation of a Small Office/Home Office (SOHO) network using Cisco Packet Tracer. The network supports three departments, integrates wired and wireless clients, and employs DHCP and VLAN segmentation to optimize traffic flow and network management.

Objectives
Develop a robust and efficient SOHO network with separate segments for departments.

Configure VLANs for traffic isolation and efficient resource management.

Implement inter-VLAN routing using router-on-a-stick.

Set up DHCP for automatic IP address assignment to hosts.

Integrate wireless access with secure Wi-Fi authentication (WPA2).

Enable connectivity between all devices, including PCs, laptops, and a network printer.

Technologies Implemented
VLAN configuration and port assignments

Inter-VLAN routing (router subinterfaces with 802.1Q encapsulation)

DHCP server setup on router

Wireless network (Wi-Fi SSID, security, access point)

IP addressing and subnetting for hosts and departments

Testing and verification of network communication across all segments

Features
Three departmental VLANs (IT, Finance, Customer Service)

Wired and wireless device integration

Secure wireless authentication

Network printer with static IP

DHCP pool and automatic host configuration

Troubleshooting steps included for practical learning

Getting Started
Use Cisco Packet Tracer to build the project topology.

Apply configuration commands as provided in the README.

Test connectivity between devices and troubleshoot any issues.
